# Web Next.js Rules

- This app uses Next.js App Router patterns only.
- Prefer Server Components by default. Add `"use client"` only when state, effects, browser APIs, or client navigation are required.
- Follow route conventions for `app/`, `layout.tsx`, `page.tsx`, and route handlers instead of inventing custom structure.
- Keep auth and routing UX explicit. Prefer server-side redirects when they avoid client-side blank states.
- Match existing dashboard code style before introducing new patterns or libraries.
- Respect existing visual language: warm, editorial, restrained, and not generic SaaS styling.
